[[File:1st parallel Tanzania.png|thumb|The 1st parallel south forms most of [[Tanzania]]'s northern border with [[Uganda]], and a short section of its border with [[Kenya]].]]
The '''1st parallel south''' is a [[circle of latitude]] that is 1 [[degree (angle)|degree]] [[south]] of the [[Earth|Earth's]] [[equator|equatorial plane]]. It crosses the [[Atlantic Ocean]], [[Africa]], the [[Indian Ocean]], [[Southeast Asia]], [[Australasia]], the [[Pacific Ocean]] and [[South America]].

The parallel defines most of the border between [[Uganda]] and [[Tanzania]], and a very short section of the border between [[Kenya]] and [[Tanzania]].

==Around the world==
Starting at the [[Prime Meridian]] and heading eastwards, the parallel 1° south passes through:

