[[File:Vojvoda_Babunski.jpg|thumb|The surname originated from [[Jovan Babunski]].]] '''Babunski''' ({{cyrl|Бабунски}}) is Macedonian surname, a [[toponymic surname]] derived from the [[Babuna]] mountain near [[Veles (city)|Veles]]. It was adopted as a surname by the descendants of Serbian Chetnik ''vojvoda'' [[Jovan Babunski|Jovan Stojković]], from his ''[[nom de guerre]]'' (or "Chetnik name") "Babunski".<ref name=RdV>{{cite book|title=Recueil de Vardar|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=k2lpAAAAMAAJ|year=2006|publisher=Akademija|page=99}}</ref> Jovan is the great-grandfather of footballer Boban Babunski, who in turn is the father of brothers David and Dorian.<ref>{{cite web|title=DEDA NOSIO KOKARDU, A ONI ĆE ZVEZDU: Unuci četničkog vojvode na korak do Marakane?|date=2015-12-29|publisher=Kurir|url=http://www.kurir.rs/sport/fudbal/deda-nosio-kokardu-a-oni-ce-zvezdu-unuci-cetnickog-vojvode-na-korak-do-marakane-clanak-2076907}}</ref> People with the surname include:
* [[Jovan Babunski]] (1878–1920), Macedonian Serb Chetnik leader * [[Boban Babunski]], Macedonian footballer * [[David Babunski]], Macedonian footballer * [[Dorian Babunski]], Macedonian footballer {{Surname}}
