{{unreferenced|date=September 2009}} {{Infobox protected area | name = Malla Strict Nature Reserve | iucn_category = Ia | iucn_ref = <!-- images --> | photo = View from saana.JPG | photo_caption = Malla Strict Nature Reserve, seen from [[Saana]] fell across [[Lake Kilpisjärvi]]. <!-- map --> | map = Finland | map_image = | map_size = | map_caption = Location in Finland | relief = 1 <!-- location --> | location = [[Lapland (Finland)|Lapland]], Finland | nearest_city = | nearest_town = | coordinates = {{coord|69|3|56|N|20|40|16|E|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <!-- stats --> | length = | length_mi = | length_km = | width = | width_mi = | width_km = | area_km2 = 29 | area_ref = | elevation = | elevation_avg = | elevation_min = | elevation_max = | dimensions = | designation = <!-- dates & info --> | authorized = | created = | designated = | established = 1916 | named_for = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = Metla | administrator = | operator = | owner = <!-- website, embedded --> | website = | embedded = }}
'''Malla Strict Nature Reserve''' (''Mallan luonnonpuisto'') is a [[strict nature reserves of Finland|strict nature reserve]] located in [[Lapland (Finland)|Lapland]], [[Finland]]. The area has been protected since 1916 and was declared a strict nature reserve in 1938. It encompasses {{convert|30|km2|mi2}} and is managed by [[Metla]]. There is a trail in the park, access to this has to be separately organized. Most of the species found here can also be found on various places around Saana, which is accessible.
{{Strict nature reserves of Finland}} [[Category:Enontekiö]] [[Category:Protected areas of the Arctic]] [[Category:Strict nature reserves of Finland]] [[Category:Geography of Lapland (Finland)]]
{{Lapland-geo-stub}} {{Europe-protected-area-stub}}

{{notability|1=Places|date=October 2017}}
{{update|date=June 2017}} {{Infobox building | name = Museum Tower Charlotte | logo = | logo_size = | image = Museum Tower Complete.jpg | status = Completed | building_type = Residential | location = 525 South Church Street, [[Charlotte, North Carolina|Charlotte, NC]] 28202, [[United States]] | coordinates = {{coord|35.224757|-80.848719|region:US-NC|display=inline,title}} | groundbreaking_date = May 1, 2015<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/news/business/biz-columns/development/article20026596.html|title=The Charlotte Observer|accessdate=2015-05-09}}</ref> | completion_date = June 14, 2017 | opened = June 16, 2017<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.charlotteagenda.com/94325/museum-tower-apartments-charlotte-nc-view|title=Luxury high-rise Museum Tower now open on top of the Mint. See the view from the 43rd floor|accessdate=2017-06-16}}</ref> | roof = {{convert|455|ft|m|abbr=on}} | top-floor = | floor_count = 43 Floors | elevator_count = 42 | cost = over $150 million | floor_area = 394 units | architect = Rule, Joy, Trammell + Rubio | structural_engineer = | developer = Childress Klein | url = {{URL|http://museumtowerapts.com}} | references = <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.emporis.com/buildings/1264993/museum-tower-charlotte-nc-usa|title=Museum Tower, Charlotte&#124; 1264993&#124;EMPORIS|accessdate=2017-03-27}}</ref> }} '''Museum Tower Charlotte''' is a 43-story apartment building in Uptown Charlotte, North Carolina. The building is 455 ft. (139 m) tall and includes 394 units.
Construction began on May 1, 2015,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/charlotte/blog/real_estate/2015/05/childress-klein-starts-work-on-apartment-rower.html|title=Childress Klein starts on Charlotte apartment tower atop Mint Museum uptown-Charlotte Business Journal |deadurl=yes |accessdate=2015-05-28}} {{dead link|date=March 2017 |fix-attempted=yes}}</ref> Museum Tower is the 5th residential building to begin construction in [[Charlotte Center City|Uptown Charlotte]] since the end of the [[Great Recession in the United States|Great Recession]].
Museum Tower Charlotte was constructed over the Mint Museum Charlotte. It opened on June 16, 2017, 7 years after the opening of the [[Duke Energy Center]] next door.
