{{more references|date=August 2014}}
[[File:Port of Belgrade and Belgrade Fortress.jpg|thumb|Port of Belgrade with [[Belgrade Fortress]] in the background.]]

The '''Port of Belgrade''' ([[Serbian language|Serbian]]: Лука Београд, ''Luka Beograd'') is a [[cargo]] [[port]] on the [[Danube]] river in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://ports.com/serbia/port-of-belgrade-luka-beograd/ | title=Port of Belgrade (Luka Beograd), Serbia | publisher=[http://ports.com/ Ports.com] | work=[http://ports.com/browse/europe/serbia/ Ports in Serbia] | accessdate= 4 August 2014 }}</ref>

The port is located in the center of Belgrade, near [[Pančevo Bridge]].{{fact|date=August 2014}} It also manages the passenger terminal on the nearby [[Sava]] river. Port transfer capacity is 3,000,000 tons per year and 10 000 TEUs. It also has 300,000 m² of warehouses and 650,000 m² of open-air storage areas.

The port has operated since 1961. There is a possibility to move the port to the other side of the Danube, providing more space for the development of Belgrade.{{Citation needed|date=March 2011}}

